cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper discusses game-theoretic analyses of distributed and peer-to-peer systems, which is a common topic in the field of computer science and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). The paper also discusses the effects of strategic behavior in distributed systems, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of sybils and collusion in the context of scrip systems also relates to the category of cs.SI (Computer Science - Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the effects of these manipulations on social welfare and security, which falls under the categories of cs.CR (Computer Science - Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computer Science - Computers and Society).
